16 WHEREAS, the recent expansion of the Food Bank of Northeast Georgia, including the
17 construction of a state-of-the-art 65,000-square-foot facility in Athens, marks a significant
18 step toward ensuring greater food distribution capacity, reduction of food waste, and the
19 enhancement of services to families across Northeast Georgia; and
20 WHEREAS, food insecurity impacts working families, seniors on fixed incomes, children
21 who rely on school meal programs, and veterans who have bravely served our nation,
22 underscoring the essential nature of food and the role it plays in both our humanity and
23 ability to reach our individual and collective potential; and
24 WHEREAS, the Food Bank of Northeast Georgia's commitment to strengthening local food
25 systems also benefits Georgia's agricultural sector by sourcing fresh, locally grown produce
26 and building farm-to-table initiatives that keep food local, sustainable, and accessible; and
27 WHEREAS, ensuring Northeast Georgia families have access to a variety of food not only
28 improves educational outcomes for children but also strengthens the workforce and increases
29 economic independence, reinforcing the vital role of food security in our communities and
30 the immeasurable impact of the family table; and
31 WHEREAS, public-private investments in food security reflect Georgia's values of
32 responsible government, strong families, and economic prosperity, as every dollar invested
33 in hunger relief leverages taxpayer dollars into the Georgia economy while expanding
34 grocery budgets when necessary.
35 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
36 the members of this body commend the Food Bank of Northeast Georgia for its mission of
37 connecting neighbors with nourishing food, its expansion to better serve families, and its
